.TH "ahci_platform_shutdown" 9 "ahci_platform_shutdown" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ahci_platform_shutdown \- Disable interrupts and stop DMA for host ports
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ahci_platform_shutdown
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
platform device pointer for the host
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called during system shutdown and performs the minimal
deconfiguration required to ensure that an ahci_platform host cannot
corrupt or otherwise interfere with a new kernel being started with kexec.
